<p style="margin: 0 0 14px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6;">Hi <strong><%= @order.buyer_name %></strong>,</p>
<p style="margin: 0 0 18px; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; color: #374151;">
  We could not verify your payment for order <strong><%= @order.order_no %></strong>, so this order has been marked as rejected.
</p>
<table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 0 0 20px; border: 1px solid #fecaca; border-radius: 10px; background-color: #fef2f2;">
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 14px 16px;">
      <p style="margin: 0 0 6px; font-size: 12px; color: #7f1d1d; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.6px;">Status</p>
      <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.3; font-weight: 700; color: #b91c1c;">Payment Rejected</p>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
<p style="margin: 0 0 16px; font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.7; color: #374151;">
  If you believe this was a mistake, please reply to this email with your transaction details and our team will assist you.
</p>
<%# <table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 0; border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b; background-color: #fffbeb;"> %>
<table role="presentation" width="100%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="margin: 0; background-color: #fffbeb;">
  <tr>
    <td style="padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #92400e;">
      You can also place a new order and ensure your payment reference is entered correctly.
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
